# Day 1 - Array Traversal

## Definition
Array Traversal means visiting every element of an array exactly once.

## Methods

### Method 1: Traverse by Value
```python
for value in nums:
```
- Returns the values of the array.
- Use when you only need the element.

### Method 2: Traverse by Index
```python
for i in range(len(nums)):
```
- Returns the indexes of the array.
- Use when you need the index or want to update the array.

## Difference

| By Value | By Index |
|----------|----------|
| Returns values | Returns indexes |
| Cannot directly modify elements | Can access and modify elements using `nums[i]` |

## Time Complexity
- **Time:** O(n)
- **Space:** O(1)

## Common Use Cases
- Print all elements
- Find sum
- Find maximum/minimum
- Count elements
- Update array values (using index)

## Interview Definition
**Array Traversal** is the process of visiting every element of an array exactly one time to perform an operation.